					<description><![CDATA[Thank you for this article: it makes compete sense to me. I started my own practice as a result of healing myself from years of serious ill health through alternative methods that I now offer to my clients, so I really see the link between improved health and entrepreneurship! I remember thinking: &quot;Now that I am in charge of my own survival and physical thriving, I can do anything!&quot; It is the attitude that you speak of.

The other obvious points for me are that: 
- I set myself hours that are optimum for my body rhythm,
- I can take a day off BEFORE I get sick instead of being in bed for 3 days
- I love my job so it does get me out of bed happy every day (which is proven to boost the immune system)
- I build walks into my day, breaks when I need them, long healthy lunches etc.

I believe that running my own business has been the key to staying healthy over the long term, yes, absolutely! I am so glad it is now backed up by research!]]></description>
